          "text": "The navigation depends on whether you're creating a new service or editing an existing one.\n\n**If creating a new service** — env vars are on the last configuration page before you click \"Create & deploy\". Look for a section called **\"Configure service\"** with an **\"Environment variables\"** expandable panel near the bottom.\n\n**If editing an existing service:**\n1. Go to [console.aws.amazon.com/apprunner](https://console.aws.amazon.com/apprunner)\n2. Click your service name\n3. Click the **\"Configuration\"** tab (not Overview or Logs)\n4. Scroll down to **\"Configure service\"** — click **\"Edit\"** on that section\n5. Scroll down inside it — you'll see **\"Environment variables\"** with an **\"Add environment variable\"** button\n\nCan you share a screenshot of what you're seeing? It'll be faster to pinpoint where you are in the console.",
