          "text": "**Use a config file in code** (`apprunner.yaml` in the `backend/` directory). It's better because:\n\n- Config is version-controlled alongside your code\n- No manual clicking in the console when settings change\n- App Runner automatically picks it up when you connect via GitHub source\n\nCreate `backend/apprunner.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\nversion: 1.0\nruntime: python311\nbuild:\n  commands:\n    build:\n      - pip install poetry\n      - poetry install --no-root\n      - git clone https://github.com/pjavanrood/lighteval.git /opt/lighteval\n      - pip install --no-build-isolation -e \"/opt/lighteval[extended_tasks]\"\n      - pip install \"setuptools<82\"\nrun:\n  command: python -m api\n  network:\n    port: 8000\n  env:\n    - name: PYTH********ERED\n      value: \"1\"\n```\n\n> **Note:** Keep secrets (database URLs, API keys) out of this file — add those in the App Runner console under **Environment variables** or pull from Secrets Manager. Only non-secret config goes in `apprunner.yaml`.\n\nThen in the AWS console, set the **Configuration file** option to use the file from your repo instead of configuring it manually.",
