          "text": "Yes exactly. The two GitHub source options (managed runtime or apprunner.yaml) both cap at Python 3.11.\n\nInstead, go back to the very first step in App Runner and select **\"Container registry\"** instead of \"Source code repository\". The flow then is:\n\n1. **Build the image locally** and push to ECR (commands from Step 1 earlier)\n2. **App Runner → Container registry → Amazon ECR** → select your image\n3. Done — Python 3.12, your exact Dockerfile environment\n\nThe tradeoff is that App Runner won't auto-deploy on git push. To update, you push a new image to ECR and either:\n- Trigger a manual redeploy in the console, or\n- Set up a GitHub Actions workflow that builds → pushes to ECR → triggers App Runner redeploy automatically\n\nFor a capstone project, manual redeploys are probably fine.",
