          "text": "Dependency installation is necessary but not sufficient. Here's what to actually check:\n\n**1. Can deps install? (catches most issues)**\n```bash\n# Create a 3.11 venv and try installing\npyenv install 3.11.9\npyenv local 3.11.9\npython -m venv .venv-311 && source .venv-311/bin/activate\npip install poetry\npoetry install --no-root\n```\nIf this fails, you have a hard blocker.\n\n**2. Does the app start?**\n```bash\npython -m api\n```\nCatches import errors, syntax issues, runtime initialization problems.\n\n**3. Hit the health endpoint**\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:8000/api/health\n```\n\n---\n\n**What can still break at 3.11 even if deps install:**\n\n- **Syntax** — any use of 3.12-specific syntax (very unlikely in your codebase, 3.11→3.12 changes were minor)\n- **Removed deprecations** — 3.12 removed some things that 3.11 still has, so actually going *down* to 3.11 is lower risk than going up\n- **Type annotation differences** — `type X = ...` syntax is 3.12-only, but you'd know if you used it\n\n**Reality check:** Your code almost certainly works on 3.11. The `>=3.12` pin in `pyproject.toml` was likely set to match the dev machine's Python version rather than because the code uses 3.12-specific features. Steps 1-3 above will confirm it in ~5 minutes.",
