          "text": "`ec2-user` is the default username for Amazon Linux AMIs — it's not something you set, it's just baked into the AMI.\n\nSo your SSH command is literally:\n\n```bash\nssh -i your-key.pem ec2-user@<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>\n```\n\nIf you had chosen a different AMI the username would be different (e.g. `ubuntu` for Ubuntu, `admin` for Debian), but since you're using **Amazon Linux 2023**, `ec2-user` is correct.",
