          "text": "`exec format error` confirms the platform mismatch is fatal — ARM64 binary can't run on AMD64. You need to rebuild for the correct platform.\n\n**On your Mac:**\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/Andrew/School/CPEN_491_Baseten/evalhub/backend\n\ndocker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 \\\n  -t 214863335048.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/evalhub-backend:latest \\\n  --push .\n```\n\nThe `--push` flag builds and pushes to ECR in one step. This will take a while since it's cross-compiling.\n\n**Then on EC2:**\n\n```bash\ndocker stop celery-worker && docker rm celery-worker\ndocker pull 214863335048.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/evalhub-backend:latest\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name celery-worker \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  --env-file .env \\\n  --network host \\\n  214863335048.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/evalhub-backend:latest \\\n  celery -A api.core.celery_app:celery_app worker \\\n    --loglevel=info --pool=solo --concurrency=1\n```\n\n> Note: App Runner also runs on AMD64, so this rebuild fixes both services.",
