        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "**1. Check container is running:**\n```bash\ndocker ps\n```\n\n**2. Check logs:**\n```bash\ndocker logs celery-worker\n```\nLook for `celery@... ready.` — that means it's connected to Redis and waiting for tasks.\n\n**3. Check Redis connection specifically:**\n```bash\ndocker logs celery-worker | grep \"Connected to redis\"\n```\n\n**4. Send a test task from the API** — the real end-to-end test. Submit an evaluation from the frontend and then watch:\n```bash\ndocker logs -f celery-worker\n```\nYou should see the task get picked up:\n```\n[INFO********cess] Received task: evaluations.run_task_evaluation[<uuid>]\n[INFO********er-1] Task evaluations.run_task_evaluation[<uuid>] succeeded\n```\n\n**5. Check for errors:**\n```bash\ndocker logs celery-worker 2>&1 | grep -i error\n```",
